1
00:00:02,171 --> 00:00:04,131
[Constantine] <i>Previously on</i>
Legends of Tomorrow...

2
00:00:04,423 --> 00:00:06,508
Astra's dead mother
was a powerful witch.

3
00:00:06,842 --> 00:00:08,194
[Natalie] Why did you bring me back?

4
00:00:08,218 --> 00:00:09,970
Natalie, is that really you?

5
00:00:10,262 --> 00:00:12,514
Natalie brought you here
to help me save Astra.

6
00:00:12,848 --> 00:00:14,558
What do you know about the Loom of Fate?

7
00:00:14,641 --> 00:00:15,869
Do you wanna know what I'm hiding from?

8
00:00:15,893 --> 00:00:17,603
- Yes, I do.
- That bloody Loom.

9
00:00:18,270 --> 00:00:19,438
He still has ten years.

10
00:00:19,521 --> 00:00:20,689
Can you make it zero?

11
00:00:20,772 --> 00:00:22,274
Bye-bye, Johnny.

12
00:00:22,357 --> 00:00:23,901
[coughing violently]

13
00:00:26,236 --> 00:00:27,988
- [fast heartbeat]
- [Ray] <i>John.</i>

14
00:00:28,071 --> 00:00:29,239
<i>John, can you hear me?</i>

15
00:00:30,115 --> 00:00:31,033
<i>What happened?</i>

16
00:00:31,034 --> 00:00:32,326
[Gary] He just collapsed.

17
00:00:32,409 --> 00:00:33,327
Out of nowhere.

18
00:00:33,328 --> 00:00:34,554
[Charlie] After coughing up
a bucket of blood.

19
00:00:34,578 --> 00:00:36,330
Come on, Johnny. Stay with us.

20
00:00:39,249 --> 00:00:40,626
Gideon, we'll need to run a scan.

21
00:00:40,709 --> 00:00:41,989
[Gideon] Right away, Dr. Palmer.

22
00:00:42,961 --> 00:00:44,338
[coughing]

23
00:00:44,421 --> 00:00:45,421
Oxygen mask, please.

24
00:00:47,216 --> 00:00:49,259
The Loom. Where is it, Charlie?

25
00:00:49,343 --> 00:00:50,904
Not now, John, all right?
You've got to rest.

26
00:00:50,928 --> 00:00:52,679
- What loom?
- Astra's ghost mom.

27
00:00:52,763 --> 00:00:55,182
She told... Oh, my God.
Hold me, hold me.

28
00:00:55,307 --> 00:00:56,367
- Hold me.
- What the hell's going on?

29
00:00:56,391 --> 00:00:58,077
[Gideon] As you can see from
his chest X-ray,

30
00:00:58,101 --> 00:01:00,979
Mr. Constantine has
a very aggressive form of lung cancer.

31
00:01:01,063 --> 00:01:02,689
I'm afraid it's terminal.

32
00:01:05,442 --> 00:01:06,902
[lighter clicks open]

33
00:01:07,361 --> 00:01:09,196
Well, there's no point in quitting now.

34
00:01:22,960 --> 00:01:23,918
[groans]

35
00:01:23,919 --> 00:01:26,005
There's nothing funny
about lung cancer, John.

36
00:01:26,129 --> 00:01:27,756
[chuckles] Who's laughing?

37
00:01:27,839 --> 00:01:28,799
[coughs]

38
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:31,594
If you lose your hair,
I'm shaving my head in solidarity.

39
00:01:31,677 --> 00:01:32,820
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hold on a minute.

40
00:01:32,844 --> 00:01:36,890
No saucy AI is butchering me
and pumping me full of drugs...

41
00:01:36,974 --> 00:01:39,351
[Gideon] I took the liberty
of administering a sedative.

42
00:01:40,769 --> 00:01:43,272
Mr. Constantine needs to rest.

43
00:01:45,357 --> 00:01:46,984
Gideon, prepare the Jumpship.

44
00:01:47,067 --> 00:01:48,402
[female voice] <i>Clotho...</i>

45
00:01:49,361 --> 00:01:52,072
<i>Where are you going?</i>

46
00:01:52,322 --> 00:01:54,616
<i>You can't escape us.</i>

47
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:56,410
[female voice 2] <i>Clotho...</i>

48
00:01:56,493 --> 00:01:58,245
<i>You can't get away.</i>

49
00:01:58,829 --> 00:01:59,997
<i>We see you.</i>

50
00:02:00,330 --> 00:02:01,581
[breathing heavily]

51
00:02:01,999 --> 00:02:03,208
No, no.

52
00:02:05,335 --> 00:02:07,129
- Oh, mate!
- Charlie.

53
00:02:07,296 --> 00:02:08,254
You're back.

54
00:02:08,255 --> 00:02:10,549
[sighs in relief]
How are you doing, B-easy?

55
00:02:12,718 --> 00:02:13,885
Where you been?

56
00:02:14,428 --> 00:02:17,097
I was just...
I was just hanging out at Constantine's.

57
00:02:17,889 --> 00:02:19,808
How is he?

58
00:02:20,267 --> 00:02:22,019
- Dying.
- What?

59
00:02:22,102 --> 00:02:23,645
No, don't worry. You know John-o,

60
00:02:23,729 --> 00:02:25,249
he's always got a trick up his sleeve.

61
00:02:26,273 --> 00:02:29,568
Bro, that donut you made me eat
had me hallucinating.

62
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:32,362
Starting today, I'm on a juice cleanse.

63
00:02:33,363 --> 00:02:34,698
Zari, this is my...

64
00:02:35,490 --> 00:02:37,284
friend, Charlie.

65
00:02:37,909 --> 00:02:39,328
Charlie, meet my sister.

66
00:02:39,494 --> 00:02:40,620
Mmm. Good fashion.

67
00:02:40,787 --> 00:02:42,307
[Agent Sharpe] <i>Team meeting
on the bridge.</i>

68
00:02:42,331 --> 00:02:43,415
Does that mean me?

69
00:02:43,498 --> 00:02:45,083
<i>That means you, too, Zari.</i>

70
00:02:45,250 --> 00:02:46,250
Cool.

71
00:02:48,462 --> 00:02:50,130
So, you coming?

72
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:53,050
I wouldn't miss it. [chuckles]

73
00:02:57,346 --> 00:02:58,346
Ah, Charlie.

74
00:02:58,597 --> 00:03:00,223
We could really use your help right now.

75
00:03:00,307 --> 00:03:03,352
With Sara in Star City and
Rory in a mood, we are short-staffed.

76
00:03:03,435 --> 00:03:04,603
What's Mick in a mood about?

77
00:03:05,103 --> 00:03:07,189
Ali. His girlfriend.

78
00:03:07,272 --> 00:03:09,316
Ray, they only...
they only had sex once.

79
00:03:09,399 --> 00:03:11,401
Well, when you know, you know. You know?

80
00:03:11,485 --> 00:03:12,485
[clears throat]

81
00:03:13,278 --> 00:03:14,278
[Agent Sharpe] Okay.

82
00:03:14,279 --> 00:03:16,365
Listen, I know
we're all worried about John. Okay?

83
00:03:16,448 --> 00:03:18,658
And we could just sit back
and wait for a miracle.

84
00:03:18,742 --> 00:03:21,661
But does Marie Kondo rest
just because she built an empire?

85
00:03:21,745 --> 00:03:22,661
- No.
- No.

86
00:03:22,662 --> 00:03:23,955
No, she tidies up.

87
00:03:24,039 --> 00:03:26,124
And that is exactly
what we're gonna continue to do.

88
00:03:26,208 --> 00:03:28,543
We are gonna tidy up the timeline, yeah?

89
00:03:28,919 --> 00:03:31,004
Gideon, show them
what we've been working on.

90
00:03:32,089 --> 00:03:34,424
Each point represents
a potential Encore,

91
00:03:34,508 --> 00:03:37,386
which means we can catch them
before they change history.

92
00:03:37,969 --> 00:03:39,596
I call her...

93
00:03:40,639 --> 00:03:42,849
The Prognosticator.

94
00:03:49,606 --> 00:03:50,564
Okay.

95
00:03:50,565 --> 00:03:54,861
Uh, anyway, there's a Category 5
in 1997, Hong Kong.

96
00:03:56,571 --> 00:03:58,931
A mysterious gangster is moving in
on the Triad's territory.

97
00:03:59,991 --> 00:04:01,451
Ray, I want you and Zari to QB.

98
00:04:01,535 --> 00:04:03,096
Oh, you don't have to tell me
to Queen Bee,

99
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,538
it'll occur naturally.

100
00:04:04,621 --> 00:04:07,541
You know what? Hong Kong traffic
is notoriously bad.

101
00:04:08,375 --> 00:04:11,962
- So why don't we take my new scooter?
- Whoa!

102
00:04:12,421 --> 00:04:13,672
I call her...

103
00:04:14,423 --> 00:04:16,216
Scoots McGoots.

104
00:04:16,299 --> 00:04:17,426
[gasping]

105
00:04:17,509 --> 00:04:19,029
- [chuckles] Dude!
- That's so awesome.

106
00:04:21,221 --> 00:04:23,140
The scooter, you're all impressed by?

107
00:04:24,015 --> 00:04:25,434
[Zari] Oh, my God. I need one.

108
00:04:25,559 --> 00:04:26,810
Wanna go for a ride?

109
00:04:26,893 --> 00:04:27,978
- Yeah.
- Yes.

110
00:04:29,062 --> 00:04:30,605
Ooh! [chuckles]

111
00:04:30,689 --> 00:04:32,691
- Away we go.
- [chuckles]

112
00:04:32,774 --> 00:04:33,900
Okay, I'm next.

113
00:04:33,984 --> 00:04:34,942
Careful!

114
00:04:34,943 --> 00:04:36,587
- [Ray] Slow down.
- [Zari] All right, speed her up.

115
00:04:36,611 --> 00:04:37,611
[Ray] Nate. Nate?

116
00:04:52,335 --> 00:04:53,879
Never been to Hong Kong before.

117
00:04:54,671 --> 00:04:56,089
So, what's the plan?

118
00:04:56,631 --> 00:04:59,468
I had Gideon cook up
the same sedative she dosed John with.

119
00:05:00,260 --> 00:05:02,095
All we have to do is inject the Encore

120
00:05:02,179 --> 00:05:03,739
and bring him back to the ship
for nap time.

121
00:05:03,763 --> 00:05:04,681
One problem.

122
00:05:04,682 --> 00:05:06,118
We're just supposed
to hope the Encore shows up

123
00:05:06,141 --> 00:05:07,141
looking for a cuppa?

124
00:05:07,642 --> 00:05:09,644
This is no ordinary tea shop.

125
00:05:12,355 --> 00:05:14,107
It's owned by the Triad.

126
00:05:16,276 --> 00:05:18,116
[Agent Sharpe]
Nate, how's the perimeter sweep?

127
00:05:18,445 --> 00:05:20,822
No sign of a gangster from Hell yet.

128
00:05:21,531 --> 00:05:23,283
So it looks like we've arrived

129
00:05:23,366 --> 00:05:25,619
right as Great Britain
was getting ready to hand control

130
00:05:25,702 --> 00:05:27,204
of Hong Kong back to China.

131
00:05:27,287 --> 00:05:30,707
Oh, that's probably not pertinent
but keep up the research.

132
00:05:31,041 --> 00:05:33,877
- Psst.
- Gary! What are you doing here?

133
00:05:34,002 --> 00:05:35,229
John's trying to leave the ship!

134
00:05:35,253 --> 00:05:36,630
You have to stop him!

135
00:05:36,922 --> 00:05:39,633
[Gideon] You should return
to the MedBay, Mr. Constantine.

136
00:05:39,716 --> 00:05:41,593
John, what are you doing out and about?

137
00:05:41,676 --> 00:05:43,094
Oh, listen, big man. [coughs]

138
00:05:43,678 --> 00:05:45,239
Look, I know you're only
trying to help, all right,

139
00:05:45,263 --> 00:05:48,558
but nobody gets Stage IV
lung cancer this fast.

140
00:05:48,642 --> 00:05:52,312
Some sneaky git with a grudge against me
is bending the rules of magic.

141
00:05:52,395 --> 00:05:54,022
Oh, who could hate you that much?

142
00:05:54,147 --> 00:05:56,149
[sighs] The list is long.

143
00:05:56,233 --> 00:05:59,444
I'm taking the Jumpship
home to narrow it. [coughs]

144
00:05:59,528 --> 00:06:02,030
John, no, I cannot
let you leave this ship.

145
00:06:02,113 --> 00:06:04,074
You are in need of medical supervision.

146
00:06:05,408 --> 00:06:06,868
You can't let me?

147
00:06:07,577 --> 00:06:09,746
You forget who I am, old son.

148
00:06:15,252 --> 00:06:16,252
Fine.

149
00:06:17,254 --> 00:06:18,380
But I'm going with you.

150
00:06:18,838 --> 00:06:20,757
Hallelujah! [gasps]

151
00:06:21,007 --> 00:06:22,509
That was intense.

152
00:06:27,264 --> 00:06:28,348
The Encore's a no-show.

153
00:06:28,515 --> 00:06:29,641
<i>I say we split.</i>

154
00:06:29,724 --> 00:06:31,268
[motorbike engine revs]

155
00:07:02,757 --> 00:07:05,093
Thirteenth-century armor,

156
00:07:05,176 --> 00:07:07,095
Fu Manchu mustache.

157
00:07:08,597 --> 00:07:09,597
Guys.

158
00:07:09,973 --> 00:07:11,683
<i>I think I know who the Encore is.</i>

159
00:07:14,477 --> 00:07:16,313
<i>It's Genghis freaking Khan.</i>

160
00:07:27,741 --> 00:07:29,993
How the hell did Genghis Khan
get to 1997

161
00:07:30,076 --> 00:07:31,536
and learn how to ride a motorbike?

162
00:07:31,745 --> 00:07:35,040
Genghis used horses
to revolutionize warfare.

163
00:07:35,915 --> 00:07:38,835
A motorbike's the modern-day horse!

164
00:07:39,085 --> 00:07:40,962
Looks like he's meeting with the Triad.

165
00:07:51,514 --> 00:07:52,514
[grunts]

166
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:58,521
What sort of man steals my drugs

167
00:07:59,147 --> 00:08:00,732
and my nephew's ear

168
00:08:01,733 --> 00:08:03,777
only to return them to me?

169
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:06,363
I have only one interest.

170
00:08:07,489 --> 00:08:09,074
Conquest.

171
00:08:09,699 --> 00:08:12,035
Surrender the Triad to me

172
00:08:12,118 --> 00:08:14,496
and I will remake the globe.

173
00:08:14,663 --> 00:08:16,581
And if I refuse?

174
00:08:20,627 --> 00:08:21,961
We're not getting in that room.

175
00:08:22,045 --> 00:08:23,254
We should abort.

176
00:08:23,338 --> 00:08:24,464
<i>Regroup on the ship.</i>

177
00:08:24,547 --> 00:08:25,941
What, and stay in Hong Kong longer?

178
00:08:25,965 --> 00:08:27,926
Give me the syringe. Let's finish this.

179
00:08:31,721 --> 00:08:33,598
B, I'm gonna need a distraction.

180
00:08:33,682 --> 00:08:34,808
It's too dangerous.

181
00:08:34,933 --> 00:08:36,101
Any moment.

182
00:08:36,434 --> 00:08:38,561
Charlie, stop. Don't do this!

183
00:08:38,645 --> 00:08:39,645
[yells]

184
00:08:39,646 --> 00:08:40,689
Behrad!

185
00:08:49,781 --> 00:08:50,907
[grunts]

186
00:08:52,033 --> 00:08:53,326
We're the cops.

187
00:08:53,410 --> 00:08:54,786
Freeze, jackass.

188
00:09:03,586 --> 00:09:04,838
Great distraction, B.

189
00:09:13,638 --> 00:09:14,639
No!

190
00:09:18,935 --> 00:09:21,187
Genghis is leaving. I'm going after him!

191
00:09:21,479 --> 00:09:22,479
Charlie, wait!

192
00:09:22,522 --> 00:09:25,108
[constant gunfire]

193
00:09:34,951 --> 00:09:36,745
[yells war cry]

194
00:09:37,495 --> 00:09:38,788
[gunfight continues in distance]

195
00:09:42,751 --> 00:09:43,751
Charlie?

196
00:09:53,344 --> 00:09:54,471
[yells war cry]

197
00:10:03,563 --> 00:10:05,607
- I'm out.
- Me, too.

198
00:10:05,690 --> 00:10:06,858
[man] Drop your guns!

199
00:10:11,321 --> 00:10:12,321
Shoot him!

200
00:10:26,795 --> 00:10:28,421
- Huh?
- Nice timing.

201
00:10:28,505 --> 00:10:29,505
[pants]

202
00:10:31,257 --> 00:10:32,217
Scoots.

203
00:10:32,218 --> 00:10:33,802
[sighs]

204
00:10:37,096 --> 00:10:38,096
Shoot him!

205
00:10:38,097 --> 00:10:39,599
- He's immortal.
- And I'm not!

206
00:10:39,682 --> 00:10:41,267
[guns clicking]

207
00:10:43,853 --> 00:10:45,063
You're lucky.

208
00:10:48,024 --> 00:10:50,485
Maybe next time, not so lucky.

209
00:10:55,281 --> 00:10:57,367
[Constantine coughs, wheezes]

210
00:10:59,452 --> 00:11:02,956
Gary, bring me the foxglove,
a serpent's tongue,

211
00:11:03,039 --> 00:11:04,666
and the hair of an albino.

212
00:11:04,791 --> 00:11:08,211
- [coughing]
- John, need some water?

213
00:11:08,294 --> 00:11:09,294
Bollocks.

214
00:11:09,295 --> 00:11:10,463
No, mate.

215
00:11:11,005 --> 00:11:12,715
Just do me a favor
and pull up the rug.

216
00:11:12,799 --> 00:11:13,799
[continues coughing]

217
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,009
[Ray] What are you planning?

218
00:11:16,845 --> 00:11:18,221
A summoning spell.

219
00:11:18,304 --> 00:11:21,140
I'm gonna throttle the bastard
that did this to me.

220
00:11:21,224 --> 00:11:22,475
Are you really up for that?

221
00:11:22,559 --> 00:11:24,644
No two-bit demon
is getting the better of me.

222
00:11:24,727 --> 00:11:28,648
I'm John Constantine,
and I am devious to the core.

223
00:11:28,773 --> 00:11:30,233
I added honey just how you like it.

224
00:11:30,316 --> 00:11:31,316
Good. Now, give it here.

225
00:11:38,032 --> 00:11:42,036
[gasping deeply, panting]

226
00:11:45,874 --> 00:11:50,211
[Astra laughing] Johnny.

227
00:11:53,631 --> 00:11:54,883
Show your face.

228
00:11:55,675 --> 00:12:00,138
The great John Constantine,
brought to his knees.

229
00:12:00,513 --> 00:12:05,393
There are denizens of Heaven and Hell
who would kill to see this.

230
00:12:11,441 --> 00:12:12,525
Surprise.

231
00:12:18,823 --> 00:12:21,159
Astra, why?

232
00:12:21,618 --> 00:12:23,536
You're bad for business, John.

233
00:12:23,995 --> 00:12:25,622
The cancer was already in your lungs.

234
00:12:25,705 --> 00:12:27,916
I just... sped it up.

235
00:12:27,999 --> 00:12:30,460
Astra, this magic
is way beyond you, love.

236
00:12:30,543 --> 00:12:31,669
Look, whoever helped you,

237
00:12:31,753 --> 00:12:34,088
whatever you promised them
in exchange, trust me,

238
00:12:34,172 --> 00:12:35,172
it's a trap.

239
00:12:36,466 --> 00:12:38,092
I'll keep that in mind.

240
00:12:38,551 --> 00:12:43,348
You know, I would have expected
your purgatory to be a little more...

241
00:12:43,598 --> 00:12:45,141
[discordant notes]

242
00:12:45,558 --> 00:12:46,643
gruesome.

243
00:12:47,018 --> 00:12:48,937
You don't remember this place, then.

244
00:12:50,355 --> 00:12:51,940
Your mother brought you here.

245
00:12:52,398 --> 00:12:54,442
So that's your angle.

246
00:12:54,984 --> 00:12:56,861
I knew you'd try something, John.

247
00:12:56,945 --> 00:13:00,531
Astra, I can change your mother's fate.

248
00:13:02,075 --> 00:13:05,411
All right? She never dies.
You never go to Hell. Your dad, he...

249
00:13:05,912 --> 00:13:09,415
He never drowns his sorrow in booze.
Your family can be whole again.

250
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:12,085
Tempting.

251
00:13:13,836 --> 00:13:15,546
But everyone you try to help...

252
00:13:17,674 --> 00:13:18,883
you hurt.

253
00:13:18,967 --> 00:13:20,235
But this is different, all right?

254
00:13:20,259 --> 00:13:22,804
I know someone who has a lead
on a very powerful artifact.

255
00:13:23,554 --> 00:13:25,098
"I know someone."

256
00:13:25,515 --> 00:13:28,476
John, listen to yourself. It's pathetic.

257
00:13:28,643 --> 00:13:31,562
No, what is pathetic is that
someone who is so content to rule Hell

258
00:13:31,646 --> 00:13:34,816
because they're too scared
to make a go at a real life.

259
00:13:35,274 --> 00:13:37,777
