of modern warfare.

520
00:26:14,158 --> 00:26:16,038
I'll go to the docks,
I'll try to figure it out.

521
00:26:16,076 --> 00:26:17,161
[Agent Sharpe] Okay.

522
00:26:17,244 --> 00:26:19,389
Zari and I will monitor
the airspace above the motorcade

523
00:26:19,413 --> 00:26:20,413
and you'll be on the street.

524
00:26:20,414 --> 00:26:22,684
I know it's a lot of ground to cover.
If Charlie was here...

525
00:26:22,708 --> 00:26:24,752
I get it. I'm on my own.

526
00:26:29,465 --> 00:26:34,094
[Bulldog] I can't believe you stooped
to trying to make a deal with an angel.

527
00:26:37,181 --> 00:26:40,517
Gabriel would have turned you
into his slave.

528
00:26:40,601 --> 00:26:42,561
Well, at least I'd be alive.

529
00:26:42,686 --> 00:26:45,481
[scoffs] There are worse fates
than death.

530
00:26:46,607 --> 00:26:47,607
Oi.

531
00:26:47,941 --> 00:26:52,321
I will shove you where the sun
don't shine just to shut you up.

532
00:26:52,446 --> 00:26:54,323
[scoffs] You'd probably enjoy that.

533
00:26:56,283 --> 00:26:59,369
Hell of a way to spend
your last nights on Earth, though,

534
00:26:59,453 --> 00:27:01,038
you arrogant bastard.

535
00:27:02,247 --> 00:27:03,540
Especially when you could be

536
00:27:03,624 --> 00:27:06,335
with two of the only friends
you have left.

537
00:27:10,631 --> 00:27:12,716
Yeah. Nice one.

538
00:27:21,475 --> 00:27:25,312
I... I just feel so helpless, you know?

539
00:27:26,146 --> 00:27:27,815
Me, too, Gary.

540
00:27:28,357 --> 00:27:29,942
If he has to go, I just...

541
00:27:30,359 --> 00:27:31,944
I want him to be at peace.

542
00:27:32,194 --> 00:27:33,821
Well, that's not his style.

543
00:27:33,904 --> 00:27:35,656
John's gonna go out the way he lived.

544
00:27:35,739 --> 00:27:37,783
[Constantine] Like a bloody wanker, eh?

545
00:27:39,743 --> 00:27:41,161
You know, it occurs to me

546
00:27:41,245 --> 00:27:43,831
that I might owe you two
a bit of an apology.

547
00:27:44,456 --> 00:27:45,582
We accept.

548
00:27:45,707 --> 00:27:46,792
Okay. [coughs]

549
00:27:47,125 --> 00:27:48,293
Go on, sit down.

550
00:27:48,377 --> 00:27:50,017
All right.
Okay, you're hurting me. Go on.

551
00:27:50,087 --> 00:27:52,214
Sit down. Stop bloody fussing, will you?

552
00:27:52,297 --> 00:27:54,341
[coughing]

553
00:27:55,759 --> 00:28:00,389
You know, I can't remember the last time
this room was used as an actual kitchen.

554
00:28:00,639 --> 00:28:02,599
Well, there's roast in the oven.

555
00:28:02,891 --> 00:28:05,561
- It'll be ready soon.
- Mmm. [coughs]

556
00:28:09,898 --> 00:28:11,441
Did I ever tell you both

557
00:28:11,525 --> 00:28:15,696
about the time I met
the ghost of Winston Churchill?

558
00:28:19,825 --> 00:28:20,868
[car horn honks]

559
00:28:20,951 --> 00:28:22,591
[Agent Sharpe]
<i>Behrad, what's your status?</i>

560
00:28:22,744 --> 00:28:24,288
It's complete gridlock.

561
00:28:24,371 --> 00:28:26,248
[sighs] No one's getting through
on the ground.

562
00:28:26,331 --> 00:28:27,725
- The fleet must be in the air.
- Nate,

563
00:28:27,749 --> 00:28:29,167
<i>did you find the shipment?</i>

564
00:28:31,420 --> 00:28:32,838
Oh, no.

565
00:28:33,005 --> 00:28:34,005
<i>We're too late.</i>

566
00:28:34,006 --> 00:28:36,508
<i>Whatever there was,
there was a lot of 'em.</i>

567
00:28:36,717 --> 00:28:38,760
Nate, get downtown and help Behrad.

568
00:28:38,844 --> 00:28:39,802
<i>Hold up.</i>

569
00:28:39,803 --> 00:28:41,513
I think they might have left something.

570
00:28:45,601 --> 00:28:47,311
[whirring]

571
00:28:47,394 --> 00:28:48,604
What's that noise?

572
00:28:52,691 --> 00:28:54,735
Oh, my God.

573
00:29:02,826 --> 00:29:04,244
Scoots.

574
00:29:05,871 --> 00:29:08,415
Khan!

575
00:29:26,350 --> 00:29:28,352
Charge!

576
00:29:28,435 --> 00:29:30,354
[minions roar]

577
00:29:45,285 --> 00:29:47,445
They're getting through the gridlock
on their scooters!

578
00:29:47,704 --> 00:29:50,374
<i>Heading straight
for Prince Charles' motorcade.</i>

579
00:29:53,418 --> 00:29:54,418
[groans]

580
00:29:56,129 --> 00:29:57,547
Stay down, Your Majesty!

581
00:29:57,631 --> 00:29:59,091
Turn here!

582
00:30:14,648 --> 00:30:15,649
[scooter whirs]

583
00:30:15,732 --> 00:30:17,567
I could really use some help!

584
00:30:17,776 --> 00:30:19,403
Nate, tell me you're close, please.

585
00:30:20,821 --> 00:30:21,989
I'd be lying.

586
00:30:22,406 --> 00:30:24,783
B, it's your time. You got this.

587
00:30:28,996 --> 00:30:33,208
[guns firing]

588
00:30:33,667 --> 00:30:34,907
[bodyguard] Protect the Prince!

589
00:30:35,794 --> 00:30:37,587
Get down! Take cover!

590
00:30:37,671 --> 00:30:38,629
Look out!

591
00:30:38,630 --> 00:30:39,630
[yells]

592
00:30:52,269 --> 00:30:53,770
Not again.

593
00:30:57,315 --> 00:30:58,650
Look who it is.

594
00:31:00,819 --> 00:31:03,030
I'm sorry I couldn't protect you,
Prince Charles.

595
00:31:03,155 --> 00:31:04,531
It's not your fault.

596
00:31:05,073 --> 00:31:08,577
But my friends call me Charlie.

597
00:31:12,706 --> 00:31:14,583
Apprehend this imposter.

598
00:31:17,794 --> 00:31:21,298
Show your true form or I end him.

599
00:31:26,928 --> 00:31:30,432
Looks like your luck has run out,
shapeshifter.

600
00:31:31,391 --> 00:31:33,060
Where is the Prince?

601
00:31:33,602 --> 00:31:34,936
Sorry, Gengi.

602
00:31:35,187 --> 00:31:37,022
He's somewhere you'll never find him.

603
00:31:37,814 --> 00:31:39,441
[rock music playing]

604
00:31:39,524 --> 00:31:41,693
Your shapeshifting friend

605
00:31:41,902 --> 00:31:45,072
said you need to tell your team
that I'm here.

606
00:31:45,155 --> 00:31:47,282
And I told her, I'm on my beer break.

607
00:31:47,365 --> 00:31:50,660
Now, shut up, princess, and listen.

608
00:31:53,038 --> 00:31:55,540
[Genghis] I've never met
one of your kind before.

609
00:32:01,713 --> 00:32:04,257
You will be my 13th wife.

610
00:32:04,674 --> 00:32:05,884
Come again, mate?

611
00:32:05,967 --> 00:32:08,428
Your power will serve my reign well.

612
00:32:08,762 --> 00:32:14,351
Join me, as I build a new empire
that will span the globe.

613
00:32:14,935 --> 00:32:15,935
Look, I'm flattered,

614
00:32:15,977 --> 00:32:18,563
but I've had power of immortals
and gods alike.

615
00:32:18,647 --> 00:32:19,815
It blows.

616
00:32:21,525 --> 00:32:23,860
My past is complicated.

617
00:32:24,569 --> 00:32:26,321
And being in a relationship...

618
00:32:27,531 --> 00:32:30,158
Trust me, that wouldn't end well
for either of us.

619
00:32:31,368 --> 00:32:32,368
Wait.

620
00:32:32,869 --> 00:32:35,914
Did you two sleep together or something?

621
00:32:38,333 --> 00:32:40,752
Oh. What a shame.

622
00:32:40,877 --> 00:32:41,877
Kill her!

623
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:42,920
What?

624
00:32:43,255 --> 00:32:44,255
No.

625
00:32:44,589 --> 00:32:45,589
Come on.

626
00:33:02,399 --> 00:33:03,984
[Charlie chuckles]

627
00:33:23,670 --> 00:33:26,631
Unless you lot want those bullets
firing back at ya...

628
00:33:27,799 --> 00:33:28,925
bugger off.

629
00:33:30,677 --> 00:33:32,846
Run away! Run away!

630
00:33:33,763 --> 00:33:36,391
Run away! Run away!

631
00:33:36,474 --> 00:33:37,934
I told you could stop bullets!

632
00:33:38,059 --> 00:33:39,269
Not how I wanted to find out.

633
00:33:39,519 --> 00:33:41,188
[laughs] Come here.

634
00:33:45,483 --> 00:33:47,194
- Yeah, that was sick.
- I know.

635
00:33:47,819 --> 00:33:49,196
Is that Genghis' toothpick?

636
00:33:49,279 --> 00:33:50,322
Yeah, you want it?

637
00:33:50,405 --> 00:33:51,965
- Ugh, no, it's disgusting.
- [chuckles]

638
00:33:57,412 --> 00:34:00,373
You said you were gonna tell us
what's really going on with you.

639
00:34:00,957 --> 00:34:03,793
Look, I'm just... I'm still trying
to find the words, all right?

640
00:34:03,877 --> 00:34:05,587
Can you try to find them faster?

641
00:34:06,046 --> 00:34:07,046
Fine.

642
00:34:08,965 --> 00:34:10,342
I'm just gonna come out with it.

643
00:34:10,800 --> 00:34:12,636
I am a Fate.

644
00:34:16,264 --> 00:34:17,849
One of the three old Greek ladies?

645
00:34:18,642 --> 00:34:21,102
That's offensive, but correct.

646
00:34:21,186 --> 00:34:22,186
Which one are you?

647
00:34:22,229 --> 00:34:24,481
Clotho, the spinner.

648
00:34:24,564 --> 00:34:28,068
I'm super-confused,
but what do you spin?

649
00:34:28,151 --> 00:34:32,072
Look, I don't spin anything anymore
but I used to spin people's futures.

650
00:34:32,822 --> 00:34:33,949
[Gideon] On your loom.

651
00:34:34,032 --> 00:34:36,076
Oh, lovely.
Even Gideon's joining in. Yes.

652
00:34:36,159 --> 00:34:38,828
There was a loom, but I
destroyed it thousands of years ago.

653
00:34:39,537 --> 00:34:41,998
No one should have that kind of power.

654
00:34:42,082 --> 00:34:44,501
I think people should just decide
their own destinies.

655
00:34:44,793 --> 00:34:46,086
Why didn't you just tell us?

656
00:34:46,253 --> 00:34:49,673
Look, I've been keeping this secret for
my entire bloody existence. All right?

657
00:34:50,173 --> 00:34:51,508
I've never told anyone.

658
00:34:52,842 --> 00:34:55,387
Can we see your OG form?

659
00:34:55,470 --> 00:34:56,513
Absolutely not.

660
00:34:57,138 --> 00:34:58,431
Is it 'cause you're old?

661
00:34:58,515 --> 00:35:00,159
It's because your eyes will explode,
all right?

662
00:35:00,183 --> 00:35:02,119
And your ears, too,
if you could hear my original voice.

663
00:35:02,143 --> 00:35:03,228
Why are you running?

664
00:35:04,646 --> 00:35:06,648
My sisters are coming after me.

665
00:35:06,731 --> 00:35:08,571
They have been
ever since I destroyed our loom.

666
00:35:08,692 --> 00:35:11,194
Wait, you've been running
for thousands of years?

667
00:35:11,319 --> 00:35:14,322
Yes. And I've always stayed
one step ahead.

668
00:35:14,406 --> 00:35:15,406
[exhales]

669
00:35:15,782 --> 00:35:17,760
I scattered the loom pieces
across the multi-verse,

670
00:35:17,784 --> 00:35:19,494
which took away my sisters' powers.

671
00:35:19,744 --> 00:35:22,205
But now that we're all in one universe,

672
00:35:22,289 --> 00:35:25,000
thanks to Sara
and her merry band of Paragons,

673
00:35:25,083 --> 00:35:27,002
the Loom pieces are back on one plane.

674
00:35:27,585 --> 00:35:30,297
And now it's only a matter of time
until my sisters find me.

675
00:35:30,964 --> 00:35:32,090
And when they do?

676
00:35:32,257 --> 00:35:35,051
They'll kill me
and anyone that I'm with.

677
00:35:36,594 --> 00:35:38,179
Which is why I left.

678
00:35:40,223 --> 00:35:43,310
And it's why I'm out that door now
that we're done playing "Ask a Fate."

679
00:35:45,979 --> 00:35:47,063
Stop running.

680
00:35:47,647 --> 00:35:48,732
We got your back.

681
00:35:52,444 --> 00:35:54,279
That is exactly what I'm afraid of.

682
00:35:55,322 --> 00:35:57,324
My sisters are no joke.

683
00:35:57,490 --> 00:35:59,284
Well, we're the Legends.

684
00:35:59,451 --> 00:36:00,493
[Nate] Yeah.

685
00:36:00,618 --> 00:36:03,204
We can take out a couple old ladies.

686
00:36:06,207 --> 00:36:07,375
[scooter clatters]

687
00:36:10,545 --> 00:36:14,299
What is with all these damn scooters?
They're a menace!

688
00:36:15,091 --> 00:36:18,136
Oh. Hey, guys. What'd I miss?

689
00:36:18,720 --> 00:36:20,781
- [all talking at once]
- Well, I lost my scooter at first.

690
00:36:20,805 --> 00:36:23,016
But the good news is,
don't worry about it, I found it.

691
00:36:27,937 --> 00:36:29,814
John, this wine is delicious.

692
00:36:29,981 --> 00:36:31,483
And nutritious.

693
00:36:31,816 --> 00:36:35,195
Well, there's no point
in saving the good stuff, eh?

694
00:36:35,278 --> 00:36:36,905
I'm never gonna drink with you again.

695
00:36:36,988 --> 00:36:39,240
Come on, mate. Stiff upper lip, eh?

696
00:36:39,449 --> 00:36:41,076
I'm gonna miss you so much, you know?

697
00:36:41,159 --> 00:36:42,952
Nothing can make me feel better.

698
00:36:43,036 --> 00:36:44,305
Oh, bollocks, all right. [coughs]

699
00:36:44,329 --> 00:36:45,329
[sighs] Look.

700
00:36:45,747 --> 00:36:48,541
I didn't want you
to see my will until I died, but...

701
00:36:49,709 --> 00:36:52,754
Raymond, if you'd do the honors.

702
00:36:52,962 --> 00:36:53,880
Uh, sure.

703
00:36:53,881 --> 00:36:55,925
[clears throat, scoffs]

704
00:36:56,508 --> 00:36:58,635
You're giving this house to Gary?

705
00:37:00,470 --> 00:37:03,556
[sobbing]

706
00:37:03,973 --> 00:37:06,768
Bloody hell. That was supposed
to make you happy, not insufferable.

707
00:37:06,851 --> 00:37:09,145
I promise to take great care
of this place.

708
00:37:09,229 --> 00:37:12,232
You know, I'll feed the Hell hounds,
I'll vacuum...

709
00:37:12,315 --> 00:37:16,444
Why don't we talk about what you had
on your bucket list, eh, Ray?

710
00:37:17,404 --> 00:37:18,655
- Really?
- Yeah.

711
00:37:18,822 --> 00:37:20,407
Give me something meaningful, ey.

712
00:37:21,908 --> 00:37:24,869
Well, uh, eventually...

713
00:37:26,579 --> 00:37:29,374
I plan on asking Nora to marry me.

714
00:37:31,543 --> 00:37:33,294
Can I be your flower boy?

715
00:37:34,796 --> 00:37:38,550
Oh. That's very sweet, Gary.
Odd, but very sweet.

716
00:37:38,633 --> 00:37:41,010
Why haven't you asked her yet, big man?

717
00:37:41,678 --> 00:37:44,889
I've been engaged twice before.

718
00:37:45,723 --> 00:37:48,643
Both times didn't end as I had hoped.

719
00:37:48,977 --> 00:37:50,562
You know, life, it is...

720
00:37:51,146 --> 00:37:53,815
too short to dilly-dally, Raymond.

721
00:37:53,940 --> 00:37:58,528
You can take that from a man
who has nothing but regrets.

722
00:38:00,155 --> 00:38:01,906
So, if you love that witch...

723
00:38:03,324 --> 00:38:05,201
you bloody well marry her, all right?

724
00:38:07,620 --> 00:38:09,956
[coughing]

725
00:38:10,248 --> 00:38:12,459
No, no, no, I'm all right.
I'm all right. [sniffs]

726
00:38:12,542 --> 00:38:13,918
Now, how about a toast, ey?

727
00:38:15,837 --> 00:38:17,088
Okay.

728
00:38:17,839 --> 00:38:18,839
No, no.

729
00:38:20,300 --> 00:38:22,886
Of all the ways that I thought I'd go...

730
00:38:24,095 --> 00:38:28,224
decapitated by a demon,
eviscerated by an elemental...

731
00:38:29,225 --> 00:38:31,728
I wouldn't have picked
being at home with my mates.

732
00:38:32,854 --> 00:38:34,355
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

733
00:38:35,356 --> 00:38:36,356
Cheers.

734
00:38:38,776 --> 00:38:39,819
[Ray] Cheers.

735
00:38:45,909 --> 00:38:48,036
[sighs]

736
00:38:48,119 --> 00:38:50,663
[coughs]

737
00:38:52,373 --> 00:38:54,167
[sighs]

738
00:38:54,250 --> 00:38:59,255
You know, I just wish
I had more time with you lovely idiots.

739
00:38:59,672 --> 00:39:02,383
Well, you're not dead yet, John.

740
00:39:02,550 --> 00:39:04,928
No, but I will be momentarily.

741
00:39:11,893 --> 00:39:13,645
John Constantine...

742
00:39:14,646 --> 00:39:17,982
he always goes out
on his own terms. [groans]

743
00:39:18,775 --> 00:39:19,775
John?

744
00:39:25,156 --> 00:39:26,950
Couldn't wait to see me, John.

745
00:39:28,076 --> 00:39:30,453
Sixty seconds and you're dead.

746
00:39:32,664 --> 00:39:34,082
Poison does that.

747
00:39:38,044 --> 00:39:41,047
It's the same poison
your mother used to kill herself.

748
00:39:42,131 --> 00:39:44,634
You won't change my mind.

749
00:39:45,343 --> 00:39:46,761
I'm not trying to.

750
00:39:48,346 --> 00:39:50,014
I just want you to know that

751
00:39:51,349 --> 00:39:53,309
even though you gave up on her,

752
00:39:54,602 --> 00:39:56,604
your mom never gave up on you.

753
00:39:58,523 --> 00:40:00,525
[coughs, groans]

754
00:40:03,903 --> 00:40:08,533
[Constantine sings]
<i>Are you going to Scarborough Fair?</i>

755
00:40:09,075 --> 00:40:13,496
[Natalie sings along]
<i>Parsley, sage, rosemary and thyme</i>

756
00:40:14,622 --> 00:40:15,622
Stop.

757
00:40:15,665 --> 00:40:19,002
<i>Remember me to one who lives there</i>

758
00:40:19,419 --> 00:40:23,756
<i>For once she was a true love of mine</i>

759
00:40:24,173 --> 00:40:26,175
That was our song!

760
00:40:26,259 --> 00:40:27,260
Aye, it was.

761
00:40:28,845 --> 00:40:31,222
But she sang it to me first.

762
00:40:32,473 --> 00:40:34,017
[ticking]

763
00:40:34,976 --> 00:40:36,185
You can really bring her back?

764
00:40:36,269 --> 00:40:37,270
[stamps]

765
00:40:38,062 --> 00:40:39,062
[coughs]

766
00:40:40,773 --> 00:40:42,108
Answer me!

767
00:40:42,191 --> 00:40:44,027
I can fix everything.

768
00:40:51,242 --> 00:40:54,579
[groans, gasps]

769
00:40:57,665 --> 00:40:58,875
I'm glad that hurt.

770
00:41:01,461 --> 00:41:02,712
Tick-tock, John.

771
00:41:03,463 --> 00:41:06,716
I can kill you anytime I want.

772
00:41:08,426 --> 00:41:09,927
[gasping loudly]

773
00:41:10,011 --> 00:41:11,054
Oh, my God!

774
00:41:11,471 --> 00:41:12,930
I can't take this anymore.

775
00:41:13,014 --> 00:41:13,930
You're alive.

776
00:41:13,931 --> 00:41:16,559
[gasps] Astra, she reconsidered.

777
00:41:16,976 --> 00:41:19,520
She reconsidered.
